== Scholarly citations, pertaining to expression in VR ==

I wrote a scholarly essay for college back in 2022 regarding this topic; this essay was about avatar and gender expression. Given this, I have some scholarly sources for anyone who reads this, to read and cite for this article. Here's the few I can still access:

* [https://drive.google.com/file/d/10Mo1_uwiuWyqieEQ3dQsz6D7iVvUUbk4/view Body, Avatar, and Me: The Presentation and Perception of Self in Social Virtual Reality] by Guo Freeman, and Divine Maloney [published 2021] (Source: [https://dl.acm.org/doi/abs/10.1145/3432938 Association for Computing Machinery's Digital Library])
* [https://drive.google.com/file/d/1KlyzqJbzMU7KFMC8GdjH7YIUotLmxbv0 Social VR Lifestyle Survey 2023] by Nem, and Mila [published 2021, 2022, 2023] (Source: [https://medium.com/@nemchan_nel/social-vr-lifestyle-survey-2021-5914c35ec063 Medium], [https://note.com/nemchan_nel/n/n167e77d78711 Note], [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=f5skcJeL3WA YouTube])
* '''[Direct PDF Download]''' [https://www.frontiersin.org/journals/virtual-reality/articles/10.3389/frvir.2020.575943/pdf Avatar Embodiment - A Standardized Questionnaire] by Tabitha Peck, Mar Gonzalez-Franco [published Feb 2021] (Source: [https://www.frontiersin.org/journals/virtual-reality/articles/10.3389/frvir.2020.575943/full Frontiers])

